# Clawbot UI / deployment — completion is non-negotiable

**Failure mode (unacceptable):** Code is pushed; engineering says done; **operator screen does not match**. That is **not** a nuance — it is **failed delivery**.

**Scope:** Any change under **`UIUX.Web/`** that affects what the operator sees (HTML, CSS, JS, or **`api_server.py`** behavior for the dashboard/API).

**Critical — `dashboard.html` vs nginx image:** `UIUX.Web/nginx/default.conf` proxies **`/dashboard`**, **`/dashboard/`**, and **`/dashboard.html`** to **`api:8080`**. The browser does **not** receive the `COPY` in the `web` image for those URLs. **`api_server.py`** reads **`/repo/UIUX.Web/dashboard.html`** from the **`api`** container’s repo mount (`../:/repo` in compose). After **`git pull`** on the host, that file is what the operator gets at **`/dashboard.html`** — verifying **`web`’s** `/usr/share/nginx/html/dashboard.html` is **wrong** for proof of the live dashboard (it can be stale or unused for that route).

**Other** static assets (`index.html`, `styles.css`, etc.) are still served by nginx from the image unless proxied — those need **`docker compose build web`** when changed.

## Work is INCOMPLETE until all five steps are done

Do **not** skip any step. Do **not** say “done” or “implemented for the operator” until the proof block below is satisfied.

1. **Pull on clawbot** — Do **not** assume `~/blackbox` is current. Run `git fetch` + `git pull origin main` (or tracked branch) and record **`git rev-parse HEAD`**. Must match the commit that contains the change (or newer).
2. **Rebuild `web` when static-in-image files changed** — `cd ~/blackbox/UIUX.Web && docker compose build web` for HTML/CSS that nginx serves from the image (not for **`dashboard.html`** via `/dashboard.html`; that comes from the repo through **api**).
3. **Restart the stack** — `docker compose up -d web api` (or full stack). **`api` must be restarted after `git pull`** when Python modules or **`api_server.py`** change — imported code is cached. Dashboard **HTML** edits are read per request from disk; bundle/schema changes still need **`restart api`**. Use `docker compose restart api` or `up -d api` after pull when the API layer changed.
4. **Verify what the browser actually loads** — For **`dashboard.html`**: e.g. `docker compose exec api grep -q '<expected fragment>' /repo/UIUX.Web/dashboard.html` **or** `curl -sk https://127.0.0.1/dashboard.html | head -40`. **Not** `web`’s `/usr/share/nginx/html/dashboard.html` for this route. For other baked static files, grep inside **`web`** as before.
5. **Verify in the browser** — Hard refresh; operator (or you via documented URL) confirms the visible change.

## “Implemented” proof (all three required)

Before claiming operator-visible UI work is complete, capture evidence for:

| # | Proof | Required |
|---|--------|----------|
| 1 | **Running commit** | `git rev-parse HEAD` on **clawbot** after pull — state the hash |
| 2 | **Runtime matches the commit** | For **`/dashboard.html`**: proof from **`api`** mount (`/repo/UIUX.Web/dashboard.html`) or **`curl`** to **`/dashboard.html`** — not stale **`web`** image COPY unless you are proving a non-proxied static file |
| 3 | **UI visibly reflects the change** | Browser confirmation (operator hard refresh) or equivalent **targeted** check |

If **any** of the three is missing, say **not complete** — not “should be there.”

